Warrior Expo showcases industry-leading solutions to end users, program managers, and procurement specialists.





This premier industry event is the embodiment of ADS’ mission to actively seek out our customers’ equipment and logistics challenges. We want to deliver innovative, cost effective solutions that enhance your ability to complete your missions.



  



Register to Attend




  



Frequently Asked Questions








  



  





 Thousands of Products





What better way to evaluate the quality, size, and capabilities of operational equipment than to experience it firsthand?
From containerized weapons storage and micro UAVs to solar powered reverse osmosis water purification systems, Warrior Expo allows you to examine hundreds of products—all in one place.








  
Warrior Expo is a laboratory of innovation where Government and Military attendees can take a deeper dive into the numerous products and services being offered at the show. The ability to speak to the subject matter experts (SMEs) is invaluable to procurement level executives in need of rapidly deployable solutions without the prospect of the hard sell.”
– Jason Sickels of Defense News






  



  
I've been attending Warrior Expo since the beginning and I have always been impressed how it is the place where requirements meet solutions. More recently, Warrior Expo has added a hands-on component to the event, and it gets better and better each year. This is a must-attend event.”
– Eric Graves of Soldier Systems Daily










 Interactive Exhibits & Demos





Your expertise coupled with our interactive environment will allow you to be more informed and confident in your procurement decisions.
Take what you learn from the interactive demonstrations and our vast exhibitor network back to your organization.






  





Educational Courses





Whether you’re an end user, program manager or a procurement specialist ADS understands that outsmarting your adversary is mission critical.Training Never Stops! Our educational courses are designed to provide the modern day warrior with applicable courses led by defense industry’s leading subject matter experts.


EDUCATIONAL COURSES






  
Threats within our own communities, our country and around the world are constantly evolving. We're very proud that Warrior Expo continues to be a resource which our nation's warfighters, law enforcement and first responders depend upon to learn about the latest innovations and technology to counter these threats.”
– Jason Wallace, CEO of ADS, Inc.









  








